Baseball is a popular sport played between two teams, each consisting of nine players. The game takes place on a rectangular field with four bases and a pitcher's mound. The objective of the game is to score more runs than the opposing team by hitting a ball thrown by the pitcher with a bat and running around the bases while avoiding being tagged out by the defensive team.

Each team has a catcher, pitcher, four infielders (first baseman, second baseman, shortstop, and third baseman), and three outfielders (left fielder, center fielder, and right fielder). The players take turns batting and fielding, with each half of the team playing offense and defense in turn. The game consists of nine innings, during which both teams take turns batting and fielding, and the team with the most runs at the end of the game wins.
